reviewText: A smarmy, womanizing art gallery director (Mark Hamill- STAR WARS 4-6, SLIPSTREAM) is cursed w/ hoodoo after he has an affair w/ a beautiful woman (Apollonia- PURPLE RAIN). His girlfriend (Amanda Wyss- A NIGHTMARE ON ELM STREET, SHAKMA) seems both clueless and helpless to save her developmentally arrested boyfriend. BLACK MAGIC WOMAN has few real thrills, but is fun to watch, especially when we see Luke Skywalker being worked on by a hoodoo exorcist! He also grimaces a lot, and writhes on the carpet! Sweeeet! We also get those blood-filled eggs and a housekeeper in the fridge! There is a dark twist at the end, but it's too little too late. Oh my!...

reviewText: Fans of Star Wars might be shocked to find their hero, Luke (Mark Hamil} play a dishonest playboy art gallery owner who is seduced by Cassandra,(Apolonia Kotero) a witch sent by his girlfriend's relatives to bring him good luck and a desire to marry Diane. Here lies the condradiction.Why does Cassandra only want to have him bitten by a snake and catch a deadly disease? Why does she in her jealousy want to murder anyone who could cure him? The relatives seemed be using witchcraft so he would want to marry Diane, yet they seem to be casting spells to kill him instead. Black Magic Woman seems to be a story to wrap around Carlos Santana's music. It's thin on plot sense, but very entertaining.
summary: Needs black magic to fix the plot

reviewText: This movie is actually pretty good! Here and there, some of the acting and lines are a little corny, but I find myself looking for this stuff, so most people probably won't notice. All in all, the acting is good. The plot line is a good one, too...keeps you going throughout the movie. It kept me engaged, awake, anticipating the next twist, so I give it 4 stars! If you have a rainy day, and some time to spare, wrap up in a blanket on the couch, grab a hot cup of tea or coffee, and fire this one up on the computer! Its worth an hour and a half!

reviewText: I had forgotten what a bad movie this was!  Unlike other reviewers, I found the acting to be substandard and totally unbelievable.  The plot was predictable and formulaic, the characters were two dimensional and predictable; I could not wait for the movie to end, and spent more time playing games on my iPhone, than watching the movie.  About the only good thing I can say about this film is that it was nice hearing Santana's Black Magic Woman, and thank god I can remove it from my watchlist!
